get.description: Returns the paginated list of Appointment instances matching the optional query (q) request param. If there is no query provided, it returns all the instances. Pagination & Sorting parameters such as page& size, sort can be sent as request parameters. The sort value should be a comma separated list of field names & optional sort order to sort the data on. eg: field1 asc, field2 desc etc

post.description: Creates a new Appointment instance.
Returns aggregated result with given aggregation info

get.description: Returns the total count of Appointment instances matching the optional query (q) request param.

post.description: Returns a URL to download a file for the data matching the optional query (q) request param and the required fields provided in the Export Options.

get.description: Returns downloadable file for the data matching the optional query (q) request param.

post.description: Returns the paginated list of Appointment instances matching the optional query (q) request param. This API should be used only if the query string is too big to fit in GET request with request param. The request has to made in application/x-www-form-urlencoded format.
Returns the list of Appointment instances matching the search criteria.

get.description: Returns the Appointment instance associated with the given id.
